1
00:00:00,810 --> 00:00:02,840
NCIS上集回顾
previously on NCIS

2
00:00:04,390 --> 00:00:05,190
我们要掉下去了!
We're going down!

3
00:00:05,250 --> 00:00:06,200
Burke牧师
Chaplain Burke.

4
00:00:06,260 --> 00:00:08,660
我刚调到海军大院的教堂
I just transferred to the chapel here on the Navy Yard.

5
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:10,280
她的遗体在那架飞机上
Her body was on that plane.

6
00:00:10,330 --> 00:00:11,110
她叫什么名字?
What's her name?

7
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,080
Gabriela Flores中尉
First Lieutenant Gabriela Flores.

8
00:00:13,130 --> 00:00:15,860
那三口棺材里 只有两位陆战队员
There were only two Marines,and those were three cases.

9
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:16,800
而Flores不在其中
And Flores wasn't one of them.

10
00:00:16,870 --> 00:00:19,650
无论任何代价我们都要找到她 带她回来
We will do whatever it takes to find her and bring her home.

11
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:21,030
陆战队员绝不抛弃队友
No Marine is ever left behind.

12
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:24,880
Flores是在帮助一所女子学校 重建时遭受突然袭击
Flores was blindsided in an attack on a girls' school she was helping rebuild.

13
00:00:24,910 --> 00:00:27,200
是与她一起共事的人?
It was the people she was working with?

14
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:28,290
这就是那个老师
That's the teacher.

15
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:30,090
任何一个在学校工作的人都可能在这照片上
Anyone that worked at that school could be in on this.

16
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:31,080
那肯定是她
That's gotta be here.

17
00:00:31,130 --> 00:00:32,210
这些是孩子们?!
Are those children?!

18
00:00:32,270 --> 00:00:34,190
她想救他们 却被捉住了
She was trying to save them,and she got caught.

19
00:00:34,230 --> 00:00:36,060
一定要带她回来
Don't come back without her.

20
00:01:19,550 --> 00:01:22,520
来吧 尽管问
Go ahead. Ask

21
00:01:25,970 --> 00:01:27,670
问什么?
Ask what?

22
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:30,300
告诉他你在想什么
Tell Him what you're thinking.

23
00:01:31,510 --> 00:01:38,210
以我的经验来说 上帝并不好夸夸其谈 他常以行动说明一切
In my experience,He's not a big talker,but His actions speak volumes.

24
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:41,730
他的行为令人质疑
His actions have been questionable.

25
00:01:43,230 --> 00:01:48,590
你的女儿Gabriela想要拯救那些孩子
Your daughter,Gabriela,tried to save those kids.

26
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:53,520
她的一生都效忠于国家
She dedicated her life to serving her country.

27
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:58,130
如果这是上帝的某种旨意 我并不苟同
If she's any indication of His actions,then I have to disagree.

28
00:01:58,450 --> 00:02:00,810
她那晚应该回大本营
She should have gone back to base that night.

29
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:01,750
她应该服从指令
She should have followed orders.

30
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,770
没错
Yes.

31
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:09,310
但或许是出于本能
But by following her instincts,

32
00:02:10,350 --> 00:02:13,330
或许是她选择听从上帝的指令
maybe she was following His orders instead.

33
00:02:21,070 --> 00:02:23,260
Gibbs能带她回来吗?
Can Gibbs bring her back?

34
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:27,160
我认识Gibbs探员的时间并不长
Well,look,I haven't known Special Agent Gibbs for very long,

35
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:30,840
但他是一个好人 他的队员也是百里挑一
but he's a good man and he's working with the best.

36
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:35,700
所以我坚信他们会尽一切所能带她回家
So I have faith they they will do everything they can to find her.

37
00:02:36,210 --> 00:02:38,600
我知道他们会找到她的 牧师
I know they'll find her,Chaplain.

38
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:41,910
问题是 她会活着回来吗?
The question is will she be alive?

39
00:02:48,650 --> 00:02:52,190
DiNozzo探员 怎么样了?
Agent DiNozzo,what is it?

40
00:03:41,340 --> 00:03:45,000
<font color=#B1D20E>海军罪案调查处 第九季 第09集 </font>
 

41
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:50,020
阿富汗 Helmand省
helmand province afghanistan

42
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:54,340
48小时前
48 hours earlier

43
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:03,430
队长
Captain.

44
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:04,870
Gibbs探员
Special Agent Gibbs.

45
00:04:04,940 --> 00:04:06,660
欢迎来到野兽之腹
Welcome to the belly of the beast.

46
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:07,790
一路顺利?
Smooth ride?

47
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,550
直到有人朝我们开枪之前
Till somebody started shooting at us.

48
00:04:09,660 --> 00:04:11,210
那是喀布尔的欢迎方式
It's Kabul's welcome wagon.

49
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,490
下回还是烤点饼干啥的吧
Next time,bake cookies.

50
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:13,680
什么情况?
What's the status?

51
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,640
一些当地人说了实话
Got some locals to change their story.

52
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:18,510
他们证实 Flores中尉和两个女孩被擒
And they confirm Lieutenant Flores and the two girls were taken.

53
00:04:18,580 --> 00:04:20,240
他们有交待出那些暴民们?
Did they identify the insurgents?

54
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:23,580
说实话是一方面 可要是供出名字就会招来灭口
Changing their story is one thing,but giving up names gets folks killed.

55
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:24,940
百姓不敢讲真话
People are afraid to talk.

56
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:26,630
那为什么没有处决Flores?
So why keep Flores alive?

57
00:04:26,710 --> 00:04:27,660
信息
Information.

58
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:30,120
激进分子不喜欢西方人让他们 的孩子开拓眼界
Radicals don't like Westerners opening up their kids' eyes.

59
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:33,740
去年整个中东地区有167学校遭袭
167 schools were hit last year throughout the Middle East.

60
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:35,750
其中的一多半都在阿富汗
More than half were in Afghanistan alone.

61
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:38,530
作为一名女性接触部队的成员 Flores知道新学校建在哪里
And as a FET,Flores knows where new ones are being built.

62
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:41,600
接触部队的作用就是在 部族和军队中起对话作用
FETs act as a conduit between the locals and the Corps.

63
00:04:41,670 --> 00:04:43,850
我会向你们介绍勤务兵Littleton
I'll introduce you to Staff Sergeant Littleton.

64
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,060
她当晚也在场
She was there that night.

65
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:47,040
学校是他们行动中必不可少的一环
Schools can be a big part of what they do.

66
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:50,990
好消息是Flores救出的那两个女孩 在以南七点方向被发现
Good news is the two girls that Flores saved were just found about seven clicks due south.

67
00:04:51,070 --> 00:04:53,450
被人遗弃在路边 她们正在被运往这里救治的途中
Abandoned roadside.They're being transported here for treatment.

68
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:54,520
她们一切还好?
Are they all right?

69
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:58,430
脱水 受到惊吓 明显遭到折磨
Dehydrated,scared,clearly tortured.

70
00:04:58,510 --> 00:04:59,710
但是保住了命
But alive.

71
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,700
我们需要见她们
We'll need to see them.

72
00:05:01,890 --> 00:05:04,090
只要你对将看到的一切有心理准备
As long as you're prepared for what you'll see.

73
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:06,230
我在这片区域长大
I grew up in this region.

74
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:08,690
看上去你没受多大影响
Looks like you turned out okay.

75
00:05:08,830 --> 00:05:10,520
我有自己的立场
I can hold my own.

76
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,370
收到
Copy that.

77
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:22,100
勤务兵Littleton吗
Staff Sergeant Littleton.

78
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:23,840
Gibbs探员
Special Agent Gibbs.

79
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,120
执行官说您想见我
C.O. said you wanted to see me?

80
00:05:25,270 --> 00:05:26,880
没错 坐下谈
Yeah.Sit down.

81
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,770
我听说学校遇袭当晚 你和Flores中尉在一起
Understand that you were with Lieutenant Flores the night the school was attacked.

82
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:38,590
我已经告诉过调查组了 先生
I already gave a statement to the Investigative Unit,sir.

83
00:05:39,020 --> 00:05:41,630
我知道 但我刚来 急于听到一切
Yeah,I know,but I just got here and I'm anxious to hear.

84
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:44,570
没什么特别的
There's nothing really different to say.

85
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,670
只是想弄清楚一些
Just trying to get a clear picture.

86
00:05:48,170 --> 00:05:49,960
好 先生
Yes,sir.

87
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:54,570
我们很多人在开火之前被疏散了出来
A bunch of us evacuated before all hell broke loose.

88
00:05:55,220 --> 00:05:57,740
我觉得我们所有人都上了车
I thought we were all together in a seven-ton.

89
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:01,260
我一直在喊她的名字 可她没有应我
I kept yelling her name,but she didn't answer.

90
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:04,010
她没有回应我
She couldn't answer.

91
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:08,810
如果我和Gabby呆在一起 或许她就不会身处险境
If I'd have stayed with Gabby,she might not be in this mess.

92
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:11,010
或许你也会丧命
Or you might be dead.

93
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:18,000
认识这女的吗?
Know that woman?

94
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,660
Soraya?
Soraya?

95
00:06:19,740 --> 00:06:21,720
她是幸运儿之一
She's one of the fortunate ones.

96
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:23,430
幸运儿? 怎么幸运?
Fortunate?How?

97
00:06:23,530 --> 00:06:25,150
她当天没在学校
She wasn't at school that day.

98
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,980
她去喀布尔郊外探访家人
She was seeing her family outside Kabul.

99
00:06:28,470 --> 00:06:30,340
那之后你见过她吗?
Have you seen her since?

100
00:06:31,660 --> 00:06:33,620
没有 先生
No,sir.

101
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:42,700
我们猜想她利用做老师的身份 来刺探袭击的最佳时间
We think that she used being a teacher to know when to strike.

102
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:45,720
孩子们相信Soraya
The kids trusted Soraya.

103
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:48,800
我们也是
We all did.

104
00:06:48,890 --> 00:06:50,280
她利用了这种信任
She took advantage of that trust.

105
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,750
而且成功做到了 先生
And she succeeded,sir.

106
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,650
她是个懦夫
At being a coward.

107
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:57,580
现在该我们出手了
Now it's our turn.

108
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:11,090
我们可能觉得每个人都应学会读和写
While we may believe that everyoneshould be taught to read and write,

109
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:14,790
可在中东还有人不这么认为
there are still some in the Middle East who do not see it that way.

110
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:17,380
从另一方面看 十字军东征时
Yeah,but on the other hand, back in the Crusades,

111
00:07:17,490 --> 00:07:21,420
圣殿骑士是为了他们所敬畏的信仰 而大开杀戮
the Knights Templar, they were willing to kill for what they held sacred.

112
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:25,320
可悲的是 在这两个例子里 无辜的孩子们却都受到了伤害
Tragically, in both instances, innocent children suffer.

113
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:27,310
年轻人的战争
A battle for young hearts and minds.

114
00:07:27,390 --> 00:07:30,830
Flores中尉发现自己处于战场中
And Lieutenant Flores found heelf at the very center of that battle.

115
00:07:30,890 --> 00:07:33,750
瞧瞧你俩-几小时后就称兄道弟了
Look at you two- hitting Wong's after hours

116
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:37,310
像大学情侣似地整夜聊天
and talking the night away like a couple of college coeds.

117
00:07:37,430 --> 00:07:40,430
我觉得Burke中校提出的观点非常...
Commander Burke offers a perspective I find quite...

118
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:42,460
令人兴奋
provocative.

119
00:07:42,890 --> 00:07:44,480
我猜也是这样 Ducky
I bet you do,Ducky.

120
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:48,120
好了 我们也有点累了 在等回应
Anyway,we're tired and waiting for answers.

121
00:07:49,410 --> 00:07:51,110
是国家安全局
That was Homeland Security.

122
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:56,240
Jaysh El-Mo'mineen和也门 沙特阿拉伯以及菲律宾的恐怖组织有联系
The Jaysh El-Mo'mineen have links to terror cells in Yemen,Saudi Arabia and the Philippines.

123
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:57,380
下一步怎么做?
What's the next step?

124
00:07:57,440 --> 00:08:00,360
我们得把其中一个组织变成 我们的激进分子
Well,we need one of those cells to turn on our radicals.

125
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:03,870
他们之间越不信任 我们就越能瓦解他们
The less that they trust each other, the more we can destabilize them.

126
00:08:04,030 --> 00:08:05,210
你有什么收获 Tony?
What about you,Tony?

127
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:06,550
我?
Me?

128
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:11,070
希望你不是浪费时间在他的 那个"人生必做清单"上 我都听烦了
I hope you're not wasting your time on that bucket list I keep hearing about.

129
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,620
那个不是浪费时间...
It's not a waste of time...

130
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,400
你有点缺少信仰哦
O ye of little faith.

131
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:16,530
现在在场的人当然没有啦
Present company excluded, of course.

132
00:08:16,610 --> 00:08:19,710
是 我是在做"人生必做清单"
Yeah,I am working on bucket list.

133
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:25,520
也许天天讨论恐怖主义 让我产生了某种不安全感
Perhaps all this talk of terrorism has me anxious about certain insecurities.

134
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:28,040
你吗 DiNozzo?
You,DiNozzo?

135
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,140
是的 我
Yes,me.

136
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:38,850
我知道-会有点吃惊-但是在我三尺男儿 的身躯里 住着一个容易受伤的梦想家
I know- shocking- but beneath this incredibly masculine body armor, there is a vulnerable do-gooder.

137
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:41,100
如何容易受伤法...?
Vulnerable to...?

138
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:48,180
是 告诉你这个就像超人告诉 死对头Lex Luthor他对氪星石的弱点
Yeah,telling you would be like Superman telling Lex Luthor about his vulnerability to Kryptonite.

139
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,800
这是不可能的
It's not gonna happen.

140
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:53,180
那么到底是什么呢 "超人先生"?
So what is it,Clark Kent?

141
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:55,900
你到底在怕什么?
What are you so afraid of?

142
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:58,140
早上好 探员Gibbs
Good morning,Agent Gibbs.

143
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,010
晚上好 主任
Evening,Director.

144
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:02,760
后面是你吧 部长先生?
That you in the background, Mr. Secretary?

145
00:09:02,820 --> 00:09:04,000
你好 Gibbs
Hello,Gibbs.

146
00:09:04,050 --> 00:09:06,170
废寝忘食啊 长官
Burning the candle at both ends,sir.

147
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:09,330
小心点 人们会觉得你太过在意了
Careful,people are gonna think you care.

148
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:12,530
围巾不错 - 有什么新消息
- Nice scarf.- Update.

149
00:09:12,580 --> 00:09:15,730
老大 我们发现"敬爱"的阿富汗老师 有一个新身份
Boss,we got an i. d. on our loving Afghan teacher.

150
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:19,620
在关于学校的一份机密军事人事档案里
This is from a classified military personnel file on the school.

151
00:09:19,690 --> 00:09:21,860
她的全名叫Soraya Zoranj
Full name is Soraya Zoranj.

152
00:09:21,940 --> 00:09:23,210
在阿富汗的巴格兰长大
Grew up in Baghlan, Afghanistan.

153
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:25,460
十几岁时 父母被俄国人杀害
Parents were killed by the Russians when she was a teenager.

154
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:27,250
Soraya还有两个兄弟:
Soraya also had two siblings:

155
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:31,420
一个哥哥Osman 两年前死于意外爆炸
An older brother,Osman, who died in an IED explosion two years ago,

156
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:36,580
还有个弟弟Asa 在美国读书
and a younger brother,Asa, who's in the U.S. on a student visa.

157
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:38,650
他将要就读华盛顿的法律学校
He's going to law school here in DC.

158
00:09:38,710 --> 00:09:39,650
跟他谈谈
Talk to him.

159
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:41,870
你觉得他可能跟他姐保持联系?
Think he might keep in contact with the big sis?

160
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,920
那就去查 - 收到
- Find out.- on it.

161
00:09:46,010 --> 00:09:49,620
McGee 我喜欢大学里清晨的味道
Ah,McGee,I love the smell of college in the morning.

162
00:09:49,730 --> 00:09:52,190
你得喝杯咖啡提神了 Tony 我也是
You need coffee,Tony. So do I.

163
00:09:52,260 --> 00:09:54,960
阿富汗作息时间把我们生物钟都搞乱了
Working on Afghan time is messing up our internal clocks.

164
00:09:55,060 --> 00:09:59,520
熬夜和在零下温度监视我都熬过来了
I used to thrive on all-night stakeouts and sub-zero surveillance.

165
00:09:59,630 --> 00:10:02,640
也许这暗示我生命中有什么东西不见了
Maybe this is a sign something's missing from my life.

166
00:10:03,090 --> 00:10:04,930
比如说 冻疮? - 你们都准备好了?
- Like What,frostbite?- You guys all set?

167
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:08,400
来吧 这孩子的室友告诉我们Asa 整晚都在法律图书馆
Come on. The kid's roommate told us Asa spent all night in the law library.

168
00:10:08,450 --> 00:10:09,890
也许应该从那开始
