354
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:52,560
需要3升的O型血
We're going to need three more liters of O-neg.

355
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:54,840
我给他点利多卡因（一种局部麻醉剂） 有人叫救伤直升机了吗?
I gotta get him some lidocaine.Did anybody call for medevac?

356
00:23:55,660 --> 00:23:56,560
在路上了
It's on the way.

357
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,690
长官 我来吧 您后退
Ma'am,I can take it from here-- step back.

358
00:24:01,070 --> 00:24:03,080
别走 David
Don't go,David.

359
00:24:04,250 --> 00:24:05,090
我不会丢下你
I'm not leaving you.

360
00:24:05,150 --> 00:24:07,470
- 长官 我要你... - 说了我不会丢下他!
- Ma'am,I need you to please-- I said I am not leaving!

361
00:24:10,330 --> 00:24:11,980
看着我 上校 看着我
You look at me,Captain.Look at me.

362
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:13,730
做得好
That's right.

363
00:24:13,980 --> 00:24:16,210
我的爸爸妈妈
My mom and dad.

364
00:24:16,470 --> 00:24:18,350
告诉他们...
Tell them...

365
00:24:18,610 --> 00:24:19,880
我很抱歉
I'm sorry.

366
00:24:19,980 --> 00:24:21,370
他们在哪里?
Where are they?

367
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:22,950
他们叫什么名字?
What are their names?

368
00:24:23,050 --> 00:24:24,210
加油
Come on.

369
00:24:24,260 --> 00:24:25,460
坚持住
Stay with me.

370
00:24:25,520 --> 00:24:27,450
马里兰州
Maryland.

371
00:24:27,710 --> 00:24:31,890
他们在海湾开了家小旅社
They own a small motel on the bay.

372
00:24:32,660 --> 00:24:34,760
一定要告诉他们...
You have to tell them...

373
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:38,150
我爱他们
I love them.

374
00:24:38,990 --> 00:24:40,530
我发誓会告诉他们
I promise I will.

375
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:42,250
我发誓会告诉他们所有事
I promise I will tell them everything.

376
00:24:57,980 --> 00:24:59,960
我们会送你回家
We'll get you home.

377
00:25:09,650 --> 00:25:11,400
DiNozzo探员...
Agent DiNozzo...

378
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:13,630
什么事?
what is it?

379
00:25:18,130 --> 00:25:19,870
我们找到她了 先生
We got her,sir.

380
00:25:20,410 --> 00:25:22,650
你女儿 Gabriela 她还活着
Your daughter Gabriela-- she's alive.

381
00:25:23,330 --> 00:25:24,850
谢谢你
Thank you.

382
00:25:24,950 --> 00:25:26,900
上帝保佑你
God bless you.

383
00:25:27,510 --> 00:25:30,320
她还活着!她还活着!
She's alive!She's alive!

384
00:25:38,150 --> 00:25:39,600
喝水
Drink.

385
00:25:40,770 --> 00:25:42,620
我有了 长官
I have been,sir.

386
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:45,530
那就再喝点
Well,drink some more.

387
00:25:46,430 --> 00:25:49,870
很多人庆幸你还活着 中尉
There are some folks happy to hear you're alive,Lieutenant.

388
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:51,980
我知道
I know.

389
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:54,240
你父亲很开心
Your dad's pretty happy,too.

390
00:25:54,340 --> 00:25:55,450
我很想见他
I'm anxious to see him.

391
00:25:55,540 --> 00:25:57,690
我想也是
Yeah,I bet you are.

392
00:25:58,750 --> 00:26:01,170
Quincy 长官...
Quincy,sir...

393
00:26:02,490 --> 00:26:05,220
如果我没有...他就不会死
he wouldn't be dead if I hadn't...

394
00:26:05,770 --> 00:26:07,080
如果我没有...
if I hadn't...

395
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:10,420
Quincy英勇就义 Flores
Quincy died doing his job,Flores.

396
00:26:11,450 --> 00:26:14,310
他是你的指挥官
He was your commanding officer.

397
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:17,210
你是他的职责所在
That made you his responsibility.

398
00:26:20,490 --> 00:26:25,680
你为何那么做...和孩子出逃 违背命令
Why'd you do it-- running off with the kids,disobeying orders.

399
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:28,320
我没有选择
I didn't have a choice.

400
00:26:28,410 --> 00:26:31,120
我清楚这些女孩会遭受什么样的不幸
I knew what would happen to those girls.

401
00:26:32,170 --> 00:26:33,770
如果让我再来一次...
If I had to do it again...

402
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:34,890
你还会这样做
You would.

403
00:26:34,940 --> 00:26:37,080
是的 长官
Yes,sir.

404
00:26:40,350 --> 00:26:45,660
我们的战士是因那个老师而死
People died beuse of that teacher-- Marines.

405
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:50,800
你认为她会有什么下场?
What do you think should happen to her?

406
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:54,490
长官 那不是我能决定的
Sir,that's not my decision.

407
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:56,860
没错 但你想过 对吗?
Yeah,but you've thought about it,right?

408
00:26:59,860 --> 00:27:02,580
她应该为她所犯下的罪行付出代价
She should be held accountable for her crimes.

409
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:18,040
她应该看着这些女孩用积极向上的 用她无法想象的方式改变世界
She should watch those girls change the world in positive ways she never imagined.

410
00:27:20,330 --> 00:27:22,110
这是惩罚吗?
That a punishment?

411
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:25,260
这是恩赐 长官
That's a gift,sir.

412
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:28,310
惩罚只会让她重蹈覆辙
Punishment is knowing she could have done the same.

413
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:37,100
你真与众不同 Flores
You're rare,Flores.

414
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:39,310
走吧 我们回家
Come on.Let's go home.

415
00:27:49,540 --> 00:27:51,180
什么事? - 没啥
- what?- Nothing.

416
00:27:51,210 --> 00:27:53,710
不对 肯定有鬼 什么事?
Oh,no.Definitely something.What?

417
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,500
你激起了我的好奇心
You intrigue me.

418
00:27:58,180 --> 00:27:59,820
为什么?
Why?

419
00:28:00,080 --> 00:28:02,080
当有东西破碎 我总想修补
When something's broken,I want to fix it.

420
00:28:02,140 --> 00:28:05,500
我不想跟你掏心掏肺 牧师 没那个金刚钻 就别揽瓷器活
Well,I hate to break it to you,Chaplain,but you ain't got enough tools in your woodshed.

421
00:28:05,540 --> 00:28:07,790
哦 你也许会吃惊的
Oh,you might be surprised.

422
00:28:12,450 --> 00:28:15,610
那么你为什么对我好奇? 因为我像天主女校的捣蛋鬼
So how do I intrigue you?In a naughty Catholic schoolgirl kind of way or

423
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:19,050
还是因为我需要所谓的"精神辅导"?
because I'm in need of what your kind calls "spiritual guidance"?

424
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:21,000
呃 幸运的是 后者
Well,lucky for me,the latter.

425
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,430
那你不需要为我担心
Well,you don't have to worry about me.

426
00:28:22,460 --> 00:28:24,320
我的精神世界坚不可摧
I am rock solid in the spirit department.

427
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:27,480
嗯 那真是太有意思了
Mm,that's fascinating.

428
00:28:28,390 --> 00:28:30,150
你知道更有意思的是什么吗?
You know what's even more fascinating?

429
00:28:30,210 --> 00:28:32,660
不知道 是啥?
No,what's that?

430
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:34,940
我不相信你
I don't believe you.

431
00:28:35,370 --> 00:28:41,000
当你准备好去面对那种恐惧 DiNozzo探员 我会和你一起面对
When you're ready to face that fear,Agent DiNozzo,I'm ready to face it with you.

432
00:28:59,660 --> 00:29:02,080
你知道 我...
You know,I...

433
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:05,040
我只是想救她们
I was just trying to save them.

434
00:29:05,130 --> 00:29:07,300
你做到了
And you did.

435
00:29:07,990 --> 00:29:09,970
躺在那棺材里的应该是我
Should've been me in that box.

436
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:12,180
不 中尉
No,Lieutenant.

437
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:15,290
躺在那里面的也不该是Quincy上校
And it should not have been Captain Quincy either.

438
00:29:26,290 --> 00:29:27,530
出什么事了?
What's going on?

439
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:28,830
说了啥?
What's it say?

440
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:31,690
直升机坠毁 六名陆战队员牺牲
Helo went down.Lost six Marines.

441
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:33,960
在哪里? - 日本冲绳岛
- where?- Okinawa,Japan.

442
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,600
他们刚到达那里 真不幸
Poor bastards just got there.

443
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:37,490
我看那个叫Matteson的女兵也在其中
I think that Matteson girl was one of them.

444
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:41,900
我其实根本没真正和她说过话 不过她三次打破我的训练记录
I never actually talked to her,but she beat three of my course times.

445
00:29:41,940 --> 00:29:44,440
她很棒 比运动员还猛
She was good.Hell of an athlete.

446
00:29:45,150 --> 00:29:46,740
Gibbs 你记得Matteson吧
Gibbs,you remember Matteson.

447
00:30:15,420 --> 00:30:18,140
敬礼
Present arms!

448
00:30:53,060 --> 00:30:55,190
敬礼
Present arms!

449
00:31:19,990 --> 00:31:22,100
欢迎来到我的教室
Welcome to my classroom.

450
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:23,960
为什么我会在这儿?
Why am I here?

451
00:31:24,060 --> 00:31:26,830
我认为我们可以先谈谈 而不是直接送你去关塔那摩
Instead of a direct flight to Gitmo,I thought we could talk.

452
00:31:27,270 --> 00:31:30,090
来个家庭团圆
Have a family reunion.

453
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:32,080
我没什么可说的
I have nothing to say.

454
00:31:33,120 --> 00:31:35,460
你们两个上次见面是什么时候?
When was the last time you saw each other?

455
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:38,310
别说 我来猜猜
No,let me guess.

456
00:31:38,390 --> 00:31:40,490
在托莱多参加恐怖分子大会?
Terrorist convention in Toledo?

457
00:31:40,580 --> 00:31:45,610
随便你怎么嘲笑我 Gibbs探员 你永远也不会明白我们的动机
Mock me all you want,Agent Gibbs,you will never understand our motivation.

458
00:31:45,820 --> 00:31:49,850
你骗取这些孩子的信任 然后伤害他们
You gained the trust of these kids,and then you hurt 'em.

459
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:54,930
教那些孩子们不要被你们的谎言所迷惑?
By teaching future generations not to be influenced by your histrionic lies?

460
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:57,850
在这个国家 孩子受教育是基本权利
In this country,teaching children is a privilege.

461
00:31:57,920 --> 00:32:02,870
在这个国家 你们浪费金钱 把孩子送入大学去享乐
In this country,you waste money sending your kids to college to have fun.

462
00:32:03,060 --> 00:32:04,940
他们学会如何独立思考
They're taught to think on their own.

463
00:32:05,050 --> 00:32:07,860
他们有钱 是被宠坏的小屁孩
They are rich,spoiled brats.

464
00:32:08,320 --> 00:32:09,700
你就是用这种方式来报复吗?
This is how you answer that?

465
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:14,530
你们这些激进派 残害杀害无辜儿童
You're radicals who maim and kill innocent children

466
00:32:14,580 --> 00:32:17,780
就因为他们想学会他人的思考方式
because they want to learn how other people think?!

467
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:20,250
你以为我们是为自己这样做吗?
You think we do this for ourselves?!

468
00:32:20,610 --> 00:32:25,490
你们来到我们的村庄和城市 带着那令人厌恶的西方思想
You come into our villages and towns with your disgusting Western ideals.

469
00:32:25,570 --> 00:32:29,240
教唆我们的孩子质疑他们的传统
You teach our children to question their heritage,

470
00:32:29,340 --> 00:32:32,150
让他们依赖于网络 抛弃古兰经
to rely on the Internet instead of the Koran.

471
00:32:32,460 --> 00:32:34,180
是的 我们就要这样报复
Yes,this is our answer.

472
00:32:34,260 --> 00:32:36,880
这就是唯一的答案
It is the only answer.

473
00:32:36,940 --> 00:32:38,720
你等着看吧
And you will see.

474
00:32:39,860 --> 00:32:41,370
我看着呢
I'll see.

475
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,150
我看什么?
I'll see what?

476
00:32:44,200 --> 00:32:45,600
你在这儿
You are here.

477
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:47,110
我们在这儿
We are here.

478
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:49,120
Flores中尉也在这儿
Lieutenant Flores is here.

479
00:32:49,170 --> 00:32:50,960
我们的大哥也在这儿
And our older brother is here,too.

480
00:32:51,010 --> 00:32:53,580
Asa 少多嘴!
Asa,don't!

481
00:32:54,300 --> 00:32:56,470
根据我们的档案 他已经死了
According to our file,he's dead.

482
00:33:00,440 --> 00:33:02,580
你以为我们的战斗结束了
Well... You think our fight is over.

483
00:33:04,450 --> 00:33:08,320
但...其实才刚刚开始
But... it has just begun.

484
00:33:21,990 --> 00:33:24,540
嗨 特种部队回来鸟
Hey,look what the Corps sent back.

485
00:33:27,710 --> 00:33:29,330
旅途艰难 Ziva?
Rough trip,Ziva?

486
00:33:29,810 --> 00:33:32,140
艰难太轻描淡写了 McGee
"Rough" is an understatement,McGee.

487
00:33:32,290 --> 00:33:34,160
Flores中尉回来了
Lieutenant Flores is back.

488
00:33:35,270 --> 00:33:37,480
还有Quincy上校
As is Captain Quincy.

489
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:41,440
问题就粗在这里
And there lies the scratch.

490
00:33:41,510 --> 00:33:42,420
是"出"
The rub.

491
00:33:42,460 --> 00:33:44,200
问题就出在这里 固定用法
"There lies the rub." It's a classic.

492
00:33:44,290 --> 00:33:45,560
我需要休息
Well,I need some rest.

493
00:33:45,620 --> 00:33:47,100
再累也不能休息 Ziva
No rest for the weary,Ziva.

494
00:33:47,180 --> 00:33:49,310
派对还没结束 他们的大哥 有什么信息
Party isn't over yet.Older brother-- talk to me.

495
00:33:49,370 --> 00:33:51,770
Osman Zoranj 38岁
Osman Zoranj,38 years old.

496
00:33:51,810 --> 00:33:53,330
出生于埃尔芒省(阿富汗)
Born in Helmand Province.

497
00:33:53,380 --> 00:33:56,070
参加圣战者组织七年 致力于反对苏维埃政权
Fought with the Mujahideen for seven years against the Soviets.

498
00:33:56,170 --> 00:33:57,920
晋升到了指挥官级别
Raised to the rank of commander.

499
00:33:57,990 --> 00:34:00,350
协助从喀布尔驱逐了俄罗斯占领军
Helped drive the Russian occupiers out of Kabul.

500
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,650
战斗英雄
War hero.

501
00:34:01,700 --> 00:34:02,990
直到他加入了塔利班
Until he joined the Taliban.

502
00:34:03,060 --> 00:34:05,070
而且他还带上了他的弟弟和妹妹
And he brought his brother and sister with him.

503
00:34:05,130 --> 00:34:07,200
跟我说点新东西 - 我有些发现
- Tell me something new.-  Well,I got something here.

504
00:34:07,260 --> 00:34:12,970
根据国防情报局消息 Osman两年前于阿富汗加德兹 在对一处复式公寓的突袭当中被杀
According to the DIA,Osman was killed in an apartment complex raid in Gardez,Afghanistan,two years ago.

505
00:34:13,060 --> 00:34:15,060
袭击引发了煤气管线爆炸
Raid set off a gas-line explosion.

506
00:34:15,140 --> 00:34:17,230
Osman是二十多名死者之一
Osman was among two dozen dead.

507
00:34:17,300 --> 00:34:19,250
可他的弟弟妹妹不这么说
Not according to his siblings.

508
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:21,040
你相信他们?
And you believe them?

509
00:34:21,100 --> 00:34:22,770
对 - 在华盛顿?
- Yeah.- D.C.?

510
00:34:22,840 --> 00:34:23,960
你来告诉我
You tell me.

511
00:34:24,010 --> 00:34:25,940
对"Oos-Mahn"发布通缉令
Putting out a BOLO on the "Oos-Mahn."

512
00:34:26,070 --> 00:34:28,410
McGee 我们需要Asa的手机通讯记录
McGee,we need Asa's cell records.

513
00:34:28,540 --> 00:34:33,000
正在处理 老大 并且通知火车站 汽车站和飞机场的执法部门
Already on it,boss.Also alerting LEOs at the train depots,bus stations and airports.

514
00:34:33,170 --> 00:34:35,460
Ziva 国土安全局和首都警局
Ziva,Homeland and Metro PD.

515
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,870
这个组织在策划什么 找出来是什么
This group is up to something.Find out what.

516
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:40,820
如果Osman的小弟弟 一直呆在华盛顿的话...
If Osman's little brother had been in D.C.the whole time...

517
00:34:40,910 --> 00:34:43,100
他也许知道他大哥在哪儿
He might know where the big brother is.

518
00:34:44,890 --> 00:34:46,240
你丢东西了吗 Gibbs?
Did you lose something,Gibbs?

519
00:34:46,380 --> 00:34:47,850
是的 一把刀
Yeah,a knife.

520
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:50,450
你口袋里一直有一把 不是吗?
Well,you always have one in your pocket,right?

521
00:34:50,550 --> 00:34:52,600
这把不一样
Well,this one's different.

522
00:35:06,820 --> 00:35:08,270
还有其他人在监视
There are others watching.

523
00:35:08,390 --> 00:35:10,720
没有 只有我们俩
Nope.Just us.

524
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:13,810
这次谈话不会有记录
No record of this conversation.

525
00:35:13,910 --> 00:35:15,560
也不需要
Don't need one.

526
00:35:20,670 --> 00:35:22,780
我们开始吧 怎么样?
Let us get started,okay?

527
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:27,240
你那狗娘养的哥哥--Osman在哪里?
Where's that son of a bitch brother of yours-- Osman?

528
00:35:37,050 --> 00:35:38,270
来支烟吗?
Want a smoke?

529
00:35:38,810 --> 00:35:41,850
不 这违反了安拉的意志
No.It is against Allah's wishes.

530
00:35:41,950 --> 00:35:44,020
对 这也违反了消防条例
Yeah,well,it's against fire regulations,too.

531
00:35:44,140 --> 00:35:46,020
不过你要是想抽一支 抽吧
But if you want one,go ahead.

532
00:35:46,070 --> 00:35:47,880
没关系
It's okay.

533
00:35:59,260 --> 00:36:00,880
看看她
Look at her.

534
00:36:01,290 --> 00:36:04,190
她身体超过60%的皮肤都被烟头烫伤
Cigarette burns over 60% of her body.

535
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:09,740
全身上下
In unspeakable places.

536
00:36:11,980 --> 00:36:13,350
睁眼看看!
Look at it!

537
00:36:13,450 --> 00:36:15,550
接着看 看着她 你这狗娘养的
Go on,look at it,you son of a bitch!

538
00:36:16,850 --> 00:36:18,150
你不能这么做
You cannot do this!

539
00:36:18,230 --> 00:36:20,230
- 住手 Gibbs探员 - 我负责 Leon!
- Stop,Agent Gibbs!- I got this,Leon!

540
00:36:20,340 --> 00:36:22,200
你马上就要违反16项国际法!
You're about to break 16 international laws right now!

541
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:23,150
他活该!
He deserves it!

542
00:36:23,220 --> 00:36:25,860
这不重要了 反正他哥哥Osman已经死了
It doesn't matter!His brother Osman is dead anyway!

543
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:30,510
FBI在20分钟前的一次突袭中 将他击毙
FBI took him down in a raid about 20 minutes ago.

544
00:36:34,410 --> 00:36:36,260
我们前去通知他姐姐Soraya 但是已经太迟了
We went to tell his sister Soraya,but it was too late.

545
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:38,370
她已经结束了自己的生命
She'd taken her life already.

546
00:36:38,470 --> 00:36:40,570
她在监狱中上吊自尽
She hanged herself in her cell.

547
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:43,030
他们都死了
They're both gone.

548
00:36:43,270 --> 00:36:45,540
我的家人死了
My family is dead.

549
00:36:46,150 --> 00:36:47,630
战斗刚刚开始 哈?
Fight's just begun,huh?

550
00:36:47,710 --> 00:36:49,950
我们会完成我姐姐开启的事业
We were going to finish what my sister had started.

551
00:36:50,050 --> 00:36:51,020
怎么做?
How?

552
00:36:51,090 --> 00:36:53,080
一枚炸弹 电子引爆
A bomb.Electronically detonated.

553
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:54,590
我的作品
My creation.

554
00:36:54,660 --> 00:36:56,200
在哪儿?
Where?

555
00:37:00,950 --> 00:37:05,810
他们没有死
They are not dead.

556
00:37:06,590 --> 00:37:08,190
他们没有死
They are not dead.

557
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,760
好的 Osman曾经的工作
Okay,jobs Osman had.

558
00:37:10,810 --> 00:37:12,010
他有权限进入什么?
What'd he have access to?

559
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:13,510
他有过几份职业
He had several occupations.

560
00:37:13,550 --> 00:37:14,660
从没做过学校老师
Never as a school teacher.

561
00:37:14,690 --> 00:37:16,720
主要做汽车修理
Mainly as an auto mechanic.

562
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,480
公共汽车
Buses.

563
00:37:19,540 --> 00:37:20,840
博物馆和纪念馆吗 老大?
Museums and memorials,boss?

564
00:37:20,890 --> 00:37:23,420
我要知道今天每所学校的旅行计划
I want to know every school trip scheduled today.

565
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:25,230
- 可有很多孩子啊 - 赶快做
- That's a lot of kids.- Do it.

566
00:37:25,290 --> 00:37:27,530
停车场方面没有显示任何异常信息
Park Service isn't showing anything out of the ordinary.

567
00:37:27,670 --> 00:37:30,380
本地几所初中 有些专业旅行
Couple of local junior highs.Some professional tours.

568
00:37:30,410 --> 00:37:31,780
我有发现
I have something.

569
00:37:32,050 --> 00:37:34,180
私立女校国家联合会
The National Consortium for Independent Girls' Schools.

570
00:37:34,240 --> 00:37:37,950
来自全国的300名女孩在科学博物馆
300 girls from around the country at the science museum.

571
00:37:37,990 --> 00:37:38,900
就是这个 什么时候?
That's it.When is it?

572
00:37:40,060 --> 00:37:42,090
- 现在 - 出发
- Now. - Let's go.

573
00:37:42,620 --> 00:37:44,200
上课去了
Class trip.

574
00:38:31,060 --> 00:38:32,890
给我电话 Osman
Give me the phone,Osman.

575
00:38:37,770 --> 00:38:40,580
把枪放下 要不我就按下最后一位数字
Put the gun down,or I hit the last number.

576
00:38:41,180 --> 00:38:44,250
Ziva 把孩子们带下车 慢慢来
Ziva,get the kids off the bus,nice and easy.

577
00:38:44,350 --> 00:38:45,700
遵命
On it.

578
00:38:47,820 --> 00:38:50,130
你不想这么做
You don't want to do this.

579
00:38:50,230 --> 00:38:52,540
这必须要完成
It must be done.

580
00:38:52,630 --> 00:38:54,920
那你也会死的
Then you'll die,too.

581
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:58,420
我会为殉教者的事业而死
Then I will die a martyr for the cause.

582
00:38:59,410 --> 00:39:00,940
McGee
McGee.

583
00:39:01,050 --> 00:39:03,000
明白 老大
Got it,boss.

584
00:39:17,140 --> 00:39:19,210
信号屏蔽器 Osman
Signal-jammer,Osman.

585
00:39:19,650 --> 00:39:21,870
这就是你的炸弹死掉的原因
That's why your detonator's dead.

586
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:31,870
你可以杀了我的
You could have killed me.

587
00:39:32,030 --> 00:39:34,350
可以 应该...
Coulda,shoulda...

588
00:39:35,740 --> 00:39:37,450
没有
didn't.

589
00:39:37,970 --> 00:39:39,570
你太软弱了
You are weak.

590
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:45,560
不是
No.

591
00:39:45,630 --> 00:39:47,560
只是比你更优秀
Just better.

592
00:39:48,890 --> 00:39:51,140
拷上他 带他离开这儿
Cuff him.Get him out of here.

593
00:39:52,010 --> 00:39:53,450
谢谢
Thank you.

594
00:39:55,210 --> 00:39:57,010
司令官的电话
That was the Commandant.

595
00:39:57,120 --> 00:39:59,910
告诉他16年前还欠我一顿晚饭
Tell him he still owes me dinner from 16 years ago.

596
00:40:00,210 --> 00:40:02,460
他亲自打电话向你表示感谢
He called to thank you personally.

597
00:40:04,050 --> 00:40:06,390
我想他是亲自打电话向你表示感谢
Think he called to thank you personally.

598
00:40:06,830 --> 00:40:07,840
这是礼节性的
It's protocol.

599
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:13,440
你要见我吗 主任?
You wanted to see me,Director?

600
00:40:13,540 --> 00:40:16,180
我希望你抽出一些时间
I want you to take some time off.

601
00:40:16,550 --> 00:40:18,040
干什么呢
And do what?

602
00:40:18,130 --> 00:40:20,730
我不知道 做点有意思的
I don't know.Do something fun.

603
00:40:22,160 --> 00:40:24,120
有意思的? - 对
- Fun?- Yeah.

604
00:40:24,250 --> 00:40:27,570
有意思的 休息 养生 钓钓鱼
Fun.Rest.Recreate.Fish.

605
00:40:27,660 --> 00:40:31,100
造点东西 我-- 随便你做什么
Build something.I-- Whatever you do.

606
00:40:31,290 --> 00:40:34,100
我就做这个 Leon
I do this,Leon.

607
00:40:34,460 --> 00:40:36,150
把休假给别人吧
Pass on the vacation.

608
00:40:36,230 --> 00:40:37,720
我还要跟Flores中尉一起吃晚饭
I am having dinner with Lieutenant Flores,though.

609
00:40:37,830 --> 00:40:39,930
她做得很好
She's doing great.

610
00:40:39,980 --> 00:40:41,770
不管怎么样 谢谢
Thanks,anyway.

611
00:40:41,910 --> 00:40:44,070
还有 Leon...
And,Leon...

612
00:40:44,710 --> 00:40:46,200
这就很有意思
this is fun.

613
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:55,640
我真的得要这么做吗?
Do I really have to do this?

614
00:40:55,740 --> 00:40:58,200
是的 放松 呼吸
Yes.Just relax,breathe.

615
00:40:58,260 --> 00:40:59,600
- 这里真热 - 不 不热
- It's hot in here.- No,it's not.

616
00:40:59,660 --> 00:41:00,780
我出汗了
I'm sweating.

617
00:41:00,860 --> 00:41:01,660
也许我心脏病发作了
Maybe I'm having a heart attack.

618
00:41:01,730 --> 00:41:03,890
我的左臂麻木 我应该去趟医院
My left arm is tingling,and I should go to the infirmary.

619
00:41:03,940 --> 00:41:06,970
你宁可看医生也不要做这个?
You'd rather go see a doctor than do this?

620
00:41:07,060 --> 00:41:08,920
天哪 D-DiNozzo 你在发抖啊
My God,D-DiNozzo,you're shaking.

621
00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:10,260
我当然在发抖 我的心脏病发作了
Of course I'm shaking.I'm having a heart attack.

622
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:12,390
你害怕了
You're terrified.

623
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:20,250
非常特别探员 Anthony DiNozzo从不害怕
Very Special Agent Anthony DiNozzo doesn't get scared.

624
00:41:21,050 --> 00:41:24,650
我曾经从飞机上跳下 险些摔死在航空母舰上
I've jumped out of airplanes,dead-dropped onto aircraft carriers,

625
00:41:24,710 --> 00:41:26,880
我还杀过人 亲爱的 很多人
and I've killed people,sweetheart.Lots of them.

626
00:41:26,930 --> 00:41:29,470
我还得过鼠疫 亲过异装癖
I've gotten the plague,kissed a transvestite,

627
00:41:29,530 --> 00:41:31,610
还被中东最好的审讯专家拷问过
and been tortured by the best the Middle East has to offer.

628
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:34,110
然后 你还是在发抖
And,still,you're shaking.

629
00:41:40,190 --> 00:41:44,670
好的 是时候直面我的恐惧了
Okay.It's time to face my fears.

630
00:41:45,680 --> 00:41:47,510
会有多严重?
How bad can it be?

631
00:41:49,580 --> 00:41:51,670
让它来吧 牧师
Bring it on,Chaplain.

632
00:42:11,890 --> 00:42:14,400
恭喜你 DiNozzo探员
Congratulations,Agent DiNozzo.

633
00:42:14,650 --> 00:42:20,310
你现在最大的恐惧 就是要吃一份葡萄和奶酪饼干
Your greatest fear is now about to have a snack of grapes and cheese crackers.

634
00:42:20,690 --> 00:42:22,870
想加入他们吗?
You want to join them?

